<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fail-v">fail <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /feɪl/    美 /feɪl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>失败；没做成</strong></h4>
<p>to not succeed in achieving sth：
反 succeed </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After failing more than 190 times,the team finally succeeded in 1971.
在失败了190多次之后，这个团队终于在1971年取得了成功。</p><footer>人教新选必① – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is very important to find out why you <strong>failed to</strong> achieve your goal.
找到你没能实现目标的原因很重要。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>未做</strong></h4>
<p>to not do sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If a store clerk <strong>fails to</strong> charge us for an item, what shall we do?
如果商店营业员少收了我们一件商品的钱，我们该怎么办？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I never <strong>fail to</strong> phone my parents on their birthdays.
我从来不会忘记在父母生日时给他们打电话。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>没有通过 (考试)；不及格；评定 (某人)不及格：</strong></h4>
<p>反 pass </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I passed history but failed chemistry.
我通过了历史考试，但化学不及格。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her work was so bad that the teacher had no choice but to fail her.
她考得太差，老师只能给她不及格。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>出故障；失灵</strong></h4>
<p>to stop working：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He saw a terrible accident in which a tram's brakes failed.
他看见了一起可怕的事故，一辆有轨电车的刹车失灵了。</p><footer>人教⑧–1</footer></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>[常用于进行时] (健康、体力、视力等) 衰退；减弱</strong></h4>
<p>to become weak：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His eyesight is failing. 
他的视力日渐衰退。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has suffered from <strong>failing health</strong>.
她的身体状况越来越差。</p></div>

<h4 id="6-let-down">6.<strong>使失望 (let down)；使无能为力：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When we needed his help, he failed us.
我们需要他帮助的时候，他却让我们失望了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My <strong>memory failed</strong> me at that moment.
那一刻我想不起来了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Words failed me</strong> (= I could not express how I felt) when I wanted to express my thanks to him.
当我想要对他表示感谢的时候，不知道说什么好。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>William found it increasingly difficult to read, for his eyesight was beginning to <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (衰退).  （2011 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. fail  </p></div>